Nadia Murad, 23, was taken by IS from her village of Kocho in Iraq in August 2014 and taken to Mosul.Murad said she was tortured and raped.Lamia Haji Bashar, who was just 16 when she was taken, witnessed family and friends being slaughtered by IS before being enslaved.The prize, worth 50,000 (about R800,000), will be presented on December 14 in Strasbourg.